IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE PARTNERSHIP EMPOWERS STUDENTS WITH QUALITY EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS, RESOURCES AND COUNSELING THAT WILL MAKE THEM CONFIDENT, KNOWLEDGEABLE AND HELP THEM FINISH COLLEGE AND CONTRIBUTE TO SAN ANTONIO'S FUTURE, MAKING THE STUDENTS SAN ANTONIO'S LEADERS OF TOMORROW.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE PARTNERSHIP EMPOWERS STUDENTS WITH QUALITY EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS, RESOURCES AND COUNSELING THAT WILL MAKE THEM CONFIDENT, KNOWLEDGEABLE AND HELP THEM FINISH COLLEGE AND CONTRIBUTE TO SAN ANTONIO'S FUTURE, MAKING THE STUDENTS SAN ANTONIO'S LEADERS OF TOMORROW.
IRS990.Desc: THE GOAL OF THE PARTNERSHIP IS TO CLOSE THE COLLEGE GRADUATION GAP FOR SAN ANTONIO BY HAVING ITS STUDENTS GRADUATE FROM HIGH SCHOOL, ENROLL IN COLLEGE, AND EARN A COLLEGE DEGREE AND/OR CERTIFICATE. SERVICES PROVIDED TO STUDENTS THROUGH THE HIGH SCHOOL SERVICES COMPONENT AND CAFE COLLEGE FOCUS ON FIVE KEY AREAS WITH THE FOLLOWING OBJECTIVES:COLLEGE ASPIRATIONS & GOAL SETTING - HELPING STUDENTS SET AND KEEP SHORT AND LONG-TERM ACADEMIC AND CAREER GOALS BY BUILDING A COLLEGE-GOING FUTURE.COLLEGE AND CAREER EXPLORATION AND PLANNING - INCREASING AWARENESS OF CAREER OPPORTUNITIES AND ASSISTING WITH PLANNING OF CAREER PATHS, TO INCLUDE INCREASING STUDENT KNOWLEDGE AND AWARENESS OF STEM FIELDS FOR CAREER OPPORTUNITIES IN SAN ANTONIO. COLLEGE ENTRY AND ENROLLMENT - INCREASING AWARENESS OF HIGHER EDUCATION OPPORTUNITIES AND ASSISTING WITH COLLEGE ENTRY AND ENROLLMENT.COLLEGE AFFORDABILITY AND FINANCIAL AID - INCREASING AWARENESS BY PROVIDING INFORMATION ON FINANCIAL LITERACY AND FINANCIAL AID RESOURCES, IN ADDTIION TO ASSISTING WITH APPLYING FOR FINANCIAL AID AND SCHOLARSHIPS. COLLEGE TRANSITION - PROVIDING GUIDANCE AND COACHING AS STUDENTS TRANSITION FROM HIGH SCHOOL TO COLLEGE WITH CONFIDENCE AND SUCCESS, AS WELL AS OPPORTUNITIES FOR CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT, INCLUDING THE ESSENTIAL SKILLS NEEDED TO BECOME AN EFFECTIVE LEADER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part XII, Line 2d: Other expenses and losses per audited F/S
Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN ORDER TO BE A RECIPIENT OF THE SAN ANTONIO EDUCATION PARTNERSHIP SCHOLARSHIP STUDENTS MUST SUBMIT A SENIOR COMMITMENT FORM, MEET ALL THE REQUIREMENTS SET BY THE PARTNERSHIP AND MUST GRADUATE FROM ONE OF THE 25 PARTNERSHIP HIGH SCHOOLS. STUDENTS MUST SUBMIT EITHER THE PARTNERSHIP CERTIFICATE OR SCHOLARSHIP LETTER TO ONE OF THE PARTNERSHIP COLLEGES/UNIVERSITIES TO RECEIVE THE SCHOLARSHIP FUNDS, WHICH IS MADE PAYABLE TO THE COLLEGE/UNIVERSITY.PARTNERSHIP COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES SUBMIT INVOICES ON A SEMESTER BASIS REQUESTING PAYMENT FOR RECIPIENTS. A REVIEW OF EACH INVOICE SUBMITTED IS MADE BY VERIFYING EACH NAME THROUGH THE SAN ANTONIO EDUCATION PARTNERSHIP CLIENT SERVICE INFORMATION SYSTEM (CSIS) DATABASE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S INDEPENDENT CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM PREPARES THE FORM 990. THE FORM IS THEN REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT BEFORE APPROVAL BY A REPRESENTATIVE OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SAN ANTONIO EDUCATION PARTNERSHIP DISTRIBUTES AND REQUESTS ACKNOWLEDGEMENT OF RECEIPT OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUALLY. ON AN ANNUAL BASIS, A REVIEW IS CONDUCTED TO BE CERTAIN ALL FORMS ARE SIGNED, RECEIVED, AND ANY ISSUES ARE RESOLVED BY THE APPROPRIATE LEVEL OF EXECUTIVE MANAGEMENT AND/OR CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THIS MONITORING PLAN WILL REMAIN IN EFFECT UNTIL CIRCUMSTANCES ARE DOCUMENTED THAT DICTATE OTHERWISE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD CHAIRMAN APPOINTS INDIVIDUALS, BOTH CURRENT AND FORMER BOARD MEMBERS, TO INTERVIEW AND MAKE SELECTIONS FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR POSITION. COMPENSATION IS BASED ON SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE LEVEL, REVIEW OF THE FORMER EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY, AND A REVIEW OF THE CURRENT SAN ANTONIO NOT-FOR-PROFIT WAGE AND BENEFIT SURVEY, SPONSORED BY THE SAN ANTONIO AREA FOUNDATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR RECOMMENDS SALARIES AND/OR PROMOTIONS FOR OTHER EMPLOYEES. THESE RECOMMENDATIONS MUST BE APPROVED BY THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST TO OUR ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICES.
